<item>
            <title>[FLINK-12915] AbstractOperatorRestoreTestBase can deadlock if one test fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-12915</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;AbstractOperatorRestoreTestBase&lt;/tt&gt; can deadlock in case of a failing test case. The problem is that if one test fails then the corresponding test job won&apos;t be canceled. Due to that a succeeding test case might not get enough slots to execute because the job of the failing test is still running. This leads to a deadlocked test as happened here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://api.travis-ci.org/v3/job/548181384/log.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://api.travis-ci.org/v3/job/548181384/log.txt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A side effect is that the original test failure won&apos;t be properly displayed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
